com.SIMRacingApps

Class Data

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.SIMRacingApps.Data
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    SessionData

    public class Data
extends java.lang.Object
    A container for all values returned from all Simulators.

    It contains the following access get/set methods. Each set method returns "this", so you can chain them.

    • Name - The name of the value.
    • Value - The actual value untranslated
    • UOM - Unit of Measure.
    • UOMAbbr - The translated short abbreviation name for the UOM.
    • UOMDescr - The translated long name for the UOM. Singular and Plural rules are applied.
    • Format - A java format string using rules defined by String.format(Locale, String, Object...).
    • FormattedValue - The value after it has been formated and translated.
    • Lang - The locale used to translate and format the value returned in FormattedValue.
    • State - A String value indicating the Value is within the range of a defined State.
    • StatePercent - The percentage the value is between the range of the State.
    • Type - The type the Value is as defined by Data.Type.
    • isDirty - Compares new value to current, returns true if different. Initially true.
    Multiple values can be added by name. The first named value added is called the default name. All of the access methods take "name" as an argument, but also there's an overloaded version that doesn't take a name and uses the default name.

    1.0

      • compare

        public int compare(Data data,
                   java.lang.String name)
        Compares this instance to another Data instance. If this instance contains multiple named values, then each one is compared in a non-predictable order. Only the values are compared based on the Type. If Type is UNKNOWN, then only equals() is used to return 0 if equal, 1 if not. An attempt is made to convert them to the same unit of measure to do the comparison.
        Parameters:
        data - The Data instance to compare to.
        name - (Optional) The specific named value to compare.
        Returns:
        -1 if this instance is less than, +1 if this instance is greater than, and 0 if they are equal.

      • toString

        public java.lang.String toString()
        Returns the contents of all the named values of this instance as a JSON formatted string. Each name will be used as the key to the attributes for that name. The format will be as follows: 
         {
     "__Id": "{m_id}",
     "__DefaultName": "{m_defaultname}",
     "{Name1}": {
         "Name": "{Name1.Name}",
         "Type": "{Name1.Type}",
         "Value": "{Name1.Value}",
         "Format": "{Name1.Format}",
         "UOM": "{Name1.UOM}",
         "UOMAbbr": "{Name1.UOMAbbr}",
         "UOMDescr": "{Name1.UOMDescr}",
         "Lang": "{Name1.Lang}",
         "State": "{Name1.State}",
         "StatePercent": "{Name1.StatePercent}",
         "ValueFormatted": "{Name1.ValueFormatted}"
     }
     , "{NameX}": {
          "Name": "{NameX.Name}",
          ...
     }
 }
        Overrides:
        toString in class java.lang.Object
        Returns:
        A JSON formatted String.
